description: A merfolk dress, it flows with such natural beauty that one might even suspect it were alive...

description: A shirt best enjoyed while sipping tropical drinks to the tune of steel drums.

description: You're lookin' spiffer, skipper.

description: If you're going to be stuck on a ship for months at a time, you may as well look cute doing it.

description: The fur is 100% repurposed shag carpet.

description: Who needs to BUY shirts when you can dig through the dumpster behind the belt shop and make one instead?

description: You're not ready to rock until you're rocking these belts.

description: Held together by scrap metal. Rock hard.

description: Can you believe people walk around wearing vests that AREN'T ripped to tatters?

name: Metal Dragon Chest Plate
description: What's harder than rock? That's right, metal.

description: One standard issue rock jacket, arms already pre-ripped off.

name: Metal Skull Chestplate
description: Clunky and completely impractical for anything other than shredding on a guitar.

name: Metal Opera Dress
description: It's not over until the metal lady sings.

description: This isn't a cheap costume! It's an official uniform worn by professional and respectful pirates.

name: Pirate Coat
description: A weathered jacket, exposed to the harshest elements of the seas. Very trendy, very chic.

name: Captain Coat
description: Spun of fine silk brought in from far across the Eastward sea.

description: A traditional kimono, worn by many during festivals dedicated to the fae spirits.

description: There are those who are able to reach through the veil of the physical realm, pulling back spirit energies from the realm of the fae. Someone turned this energy into a dress!

description: Blessed by the fae spirits, mere cloth robes have become a durable outfit worn by their defenders.

name: Spirit Half Robe
description: If you're going to be a cool spirit world-hopping fae communer, you may as well look the part.

name: Spirit Ruffle Cropped Top
description: Vestments styled in the legendary outfit of the first fae-friend.

name: Shattered Spirit Vest
description: Power is wasted on the peaceful, let those with ambition wield it instead.

description: The spirit moon festival can be exhausting, wearing appropriate clothing is a must if one is to complete the dance.

name: Candle Costume
description: Here's a clever DIY costume idea: Cover yourself in 165 pounds of melted candle wax.

description: Who will be able to tell what spooky tricks you have up your sleeves when you wear this baggy robe? No one, that's who.

description: A hauntingly white sheet, fashioned into an airy robe. In the breeze of a dark trick or treat night, you'll look just like a real ghost.

name: Pumpkin Polo Shirt
description: Fashionable, yet pumpkiny. Perfect.

name: Stitched Witch Dress
description: Conjuring spells, preparing potions, turning people into newts... it's not surprising this dress needed a few repairs here and there.

description: Dress up those bones for a special spooky occassion.

name: Candle Dress
description: Only a witch has the magical skills - and wild imagination - necessary to conjure such a waxy garmet.

description: The tattered remains of a purple robe, it's not much of a robe anymore but it'll make a nifty scarf.

name: Pumpkin Dress
description: Who needs to dress a pumpkin? Oh wait, it's not for pumpkins - it's for you!

name: Veteran Battle Star Long Gloves
description: These gloves never scuff, no matter how many faces you punch.

name: Spirit Ruffle Bracelets
description: Vestments styled in the legendary outfit of the first fae-friend.

description: If you thought your outfit was spooky before, just wait until you put on these gloves.

name: Ghost Costume Gloves
description: Are these gloves haunted or are they just apart of your costume...

name: Troublemaker Backward Hat
description: If the cyberguard catches you hacking into the Great Frame, they'll delete you down to the last byte. But first, they have to catch you...

name: Cyberpop Robo Headband
description: It looks like a child's headband toy, but in reality its ears can hear microfrequencies emitted by Great Frame hall monitor drones.

name: Cyberpop Headphones
description: Whether you're fighting against the cyberguard or battling over turf with a rival gang, you gotta blast the tunes.

name: Cyberpop Goggles
description: Not just ordinary goggles, these puppies let you see the digital controls of security jets. They'll also look really neat on your head.

name: Student Windswept Wig
description: Students of the Cyber Acadamia have two objectives: Ace their tests and look great doing it.

name: Battle Eye Scanner
description: [ERROR 502: OVER 9000 JOKE NOT FOUND]

name: Veteran Battle Star Clip
description: Special hacked clips that transport users to the digital battlegrounds of the Battle Star arena.

name: e-Battler Wig
description: Forget about the proctors and edu-bots. After class is out and you're out of view of the cameras, you can style your hair however you want.

name: e-Battler Headphones
description: Crystal clear sound quality and able to withstand forces of up to 50,000 psi.

name: Battle Exchange Student Wig

name: Battle Exchange Student Hairband
description: Ooh, is it made out of a super top secret material that lets you read minds?! ...Nope, just a strip of old cloth, but great at keeping your hair tied up and out of the way when you're in an e-Battle!

name: Tech Academia Student Wig
description: In the year 3XXX, individualism and expression have largely been outlawed. Not that it stops anyone.

name: Tech Academia Student Glasses
description: These byte-detecting goggles are definitely not part of the Acadamia dress code.
